===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|廾|口|t1=two hands|t2=an object|ls=ic}} – holding up an object with two hands. Eventually {{zh-l|*口}} (not {{m-g|mouth}}) came to be written {{zh-l|*廿}} (not {{m-g|twenty}}), which later fused with {{zh-l|*廾}} to form the modern 共.

Possibly the original form of {{zh-l|*供|to provide; to offer}}.

===Etymology 1===
Possibly related to {{och-l|廾|to fold the hands in front of the breast|tr=*k(r)oŋʔ}}, with the stativizing prefix ''*N-'' ({{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2014}}). {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} also relates this word to {{och-l|供|to provide}} and suggests the possibility of also relating it to {{och-l|恭|to respect}} and {{och-l|貢|tribute}}.

The ''kā'' reading in {{ncog|nan-hbl|-}} is from the weakening of ''kāng'' ({{zh-ref|Wu, 2017}}; {{zh-ref|Chappell et al., 2011}}).

